<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>User Insight Synthesis: PM Scheduler Initiative</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
    <style>
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            height: 300px;
            max-height: 400px;
        }
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .chart-container {
                height: 350px;
            }
        }
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #F3F4F6;
            color: #1F2937;
        }
        .card {
            background-color: #FFFFFF;
            border-radius: 0.75rem;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 2px 4px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
            padding: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease;
        }
        .card:hover {
            box-shadow: 0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 4px 6px -2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        }
        .vibrant-blue { color: #1E3A8A; }
        .bg-vibrant-blue { background-color: #1E3A8A; }
        .vibrant-cyan { color: #06B6D4; }
        .bg-vibrant-cyan { background-color: #06B6D4; }
        .vibrant-orange { color: #F97316; }
        .bg-vibrant-orange { background-color: #F97316; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- Explicitly confirming that NEITHER Mermaid JS NOR SVG were used anywhere in the output -->
<!-- Palette: Vibrant Tech (Deep Blue #1E3A8A, Brilliant Cyan #06B6D4, Energetic Orange #F97316, Alert Red #EF4444, Success Green #10B981) -->
<!-- Narrative Plan: 1. Introduction (The $1.2M Gap). 2. Data Overview (Status Quo Workarounds). 3. The Compliance Gap. 4. In-Depth Analysis (Core Friction Points). 5. Future Outlook (TSFM & AI Deterioration Modeling). 6. Conclusion (Prescriptive AI Flow). -->
<!-- Visualization Choices: 1. Financial Impact -> Inform -> Big Number (No SVG). 2. Status Quo Friction -> Compare -> Bar Chart (Chart.js). 3. Compliance Gap -> Compare/Composition -> Doughnut Chart (Chart.js). 4. System Friction Points -> Relationships -> Radar Chart (Chart.js). 5. Deterioration Modeling -> Change/Trend -> Line Chart (Chart.js). All adhering to NO SVG constraint. -->

<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">

    <header class="mb-10 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold vibrant-blue mb-4">&#x1F527; Trimble Unity Maintain: The PM Scheduler Crisis & Evolution</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">An executive synthesis of user research, highlighting the critical gaps in static preventative maintenance and the roadmap toward an AI-driven, risk-adjusted prescriptive future.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="card md:col-span-1 flex flex-col justify-center items-center text-center border-t-4 border-[#EF4444]">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Identified Revenue At Risk</h2>
            <div class="text-5xl font-extrabold text-[#EF4444] mb-2">$1.2M+</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Documented ARR loss and immediate risk due exclusively to the PM Scheduler feature gap.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card md:col-span-2 bg-vibrant-blue text-white border-t-4 border-vibrant-cyan">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">&#x26A0; The Core Issue</h2>
            <p class="text-blue-100 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                Unity Maintain currently lacks industry-standard, asset-based Preventative Maintenance (PM) scheduling. Customers cannot properly plan, forecast, or nest PMs. This absence creates immediate friction, forcing complex workarounds, widening the "Compliance Gap," and causing severe reputational damage during implementations.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold vibrant-blue mb-4">&#x1F4CA; The Status Quo: Surviving via Workarounds</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Because the current system of record is "blind" to future maintenance loads and suffers from rigid logic (like infinite "child work order" loops), implementers and clients rely on fragmented, high-friction shadow systems to survive.
            </p>
            <div class="chart-container">
                <canvas id="workaroundsChart"></canvas>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-orange-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-vibrant-orange">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 font-medium">
                    <span class="font-bold vibrant-orange">Key Takeaway:</span> The lack of dual-trigger logic ("Whichever Comes First") forces Fleet managers back to analog windshield stickers, while the lack of nesting pushes admins to build custom Python Webhooks just to suppress duplicate work orders.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold vibrant-blue mb-4">&#x1F4D0; The Compliance Gap</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Rigid, calendar-based schedules create a massive divergence between the intended O&M strategy built in the back office and the actual physical execution taking place in the field.
            </p>
            <div class="chart-container">
                <canvas id="complianceChart"></canvas>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-vibrant-cyan">
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 font-medium">
                    <span class="font-bold vibrant-cyan">Key Takeaway:</span> Over-maintenance causes technician fatigue and "pencil-whipping," where technicians sign off on inspections without performing them just to clear cluttered digital inboxes, severely compromising data integrity.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card lg:col-span-2">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold vibrant-blue mb-4">&#x1F3AF; Core User Insights & Friction Points</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 max-w-4xl">
                Through deep-dive user interviews (including insights from WSP, Centricity, and Esri Canada), four distinct functional failures were identified in the current EAM logic. These failures drastically reduce system trust and overall efficiency.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center">
                <div class="chart-container w-full md:w-1/2">
                    <canvas id="frictionRadarChart"></canvas>
                </div>
                <div class="w-full md:w-1/2 mt-6 md:mt-0 md:pl-8 space-y-4">
                    <div class="p-3 border border-gray-200 rounded shadow-sm">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-[#1E3A8A]">&#x1F4D1; 1. The "Ghost Record" Visibility Void</h4>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-1">Users need a calendar view to forecast labor without actually generating 500 database records that clutter live work lists.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-3 border border-gray-200 rounded shadow-sm">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-[#F97316]">&#x1F504; 2. Child Work Order Loops</h4>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-1">Immediate generation of the next cycle's work order creates confusing pyramids of duplicates. Canceling a PM often accidentally triggers a new one.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-3 border border-gray-200 rounded shadow-sm">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-[#06B6D4]">&#x23E9; 3. Dual-Trigger Absence</h4>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-1">Inability to trigger based on "Whichever Comes First" (Time vs. Usage) blocks major Fleet and Plant infrastructure deals.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-3 border border-gray-200 rounded shadow-sm">
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-[#10B981]">&#x1F5C3; 4. Manual "Nesting" Burden</h4>
                        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-1">Lack of automated suppression means Annual PMs don't automatically override overlapping Quarterly PMs, requiring massive manual cleanup.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card lg:col-span-2 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold vibrant-blue mb-4">&#x1F4C8; The Future: TSFM & Dynamic Deterioration Modeling</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 max-w-4xl">
                By abandoning rigid schedules and adopting Time Series Foundation Models (TSFM) combined with LSTM Neural Networks, Trimble Unity Maintain can shift from generalized age-based triggers to highly accurate, Risk-Based Remaining Useful Life (RUL) estimations.
            </p>
            <div class="chart-container" style="max-width: 800px;">
                <canvas id="degradationChart"></canvas>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded shadow-sm border-t-2 border-[#EF4444]">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 text-sm uppercase">The Rigid Fallacy (Static PM)</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">Assumes an asset wears down evenly every month. Results in tearing down healthy equipment (introducing maintenance-induced failure) or missing critical accelerated decay.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded shadow-sm border-t-2 border-[#10B981]">
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-800 text-sm uppercase">The Dynamic Reality (AI/TSFM)</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">Treats every repair, usage spike, and environmental factor as an intervening variable. A 15-year-old pipe may deteriorate 5x faster in year 16 than year 5. AI defers or accelerates tasks accordingly.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card lg:col-span-2">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold vibrant-blue mb-4">&#x1F9E0; The Prescriptive Maintenance (RxM) Workflow</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Illuminating the 90% "Dark Data" void—messy technician notes previously unreadable by standard databases—via Natural Language Processing (NLP) allows the EAM to not just predict failure, but prescribe the exact repair.
            </p>
            
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 justify-between items-stretch bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
                <div class="flex-1 bg-white p-4 rounded shadow text-center border-l-4 border-gray-400">
                    <div class="text-3xl mb-2">&#x1F4DD;</div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-sm">1. Dark Data Ingestion</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">NLP parses chaotic historical technician logs (e.g., "brg noise again, chkd alignment").</p>
                </div>
                <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center text-2xl text-gray-400">&#x27A1;</div>
                <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center md:hidden text-2xl text-gray-400">&#x2B07;</div>
                
                <div class="flex-1 bg-white p-4 rounded shadow text-center border-l-4 border-vibrant-cyan">
                    <div class="text-3xl mb-2">&#x1F50D;</div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-sm">2. Precursor Extraction</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Named Entity Recognition links minor vibrations to catastrophic failures 3 weeks later.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center text-2xl text-gray-400">&#x27A1;</div>
                <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center md:hidden text-2xl text-gray-400">&#x2B07;</div>

                <div class="flex-1 bg-white p-4 rounded shadow text-center border-l-4 border-vibrant-orange">
                    <div class="text-3xl mb-2">&#x2696;</div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-sm">3. Risk-Adjusted Plan</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Priority is calculated dynamically: Probability of Failure (PoF) × Spatial Consequence (CoF).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center text-2xl text-gray-400">&#x27A1;</div>
                <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center md:hidden text-2xl text-gray-400">&#x2B07;</div>

                <div class="flex-1 bg-white p-4 rounded shadow text-center border-l-4 border-[#10B981]">
                    <div class="text-3xl mb-2">&#x1F6E0;</div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-sm">4. Prescriptive Action</h4>
                    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">Generative AI drafts specific work orders with OEM manuals, torque settings, and BOMs.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>

<script>
    function wrapLabel(label) {
        if (label.length <= 16) return label;
        const words = label.split(' ');
        const lines = [];
        let currentLine = '';
        words.forEach(word => {
            if ((currentLine + word).length > 16) {
                if (currentLine) lines.push(currentLine.trim());
                currentLine = word + ' ';
            } else {
                currentLine += word + ' ';
            }
        });
        if (currentLine) lines.push(currentLine.trim());
        return lines;
    }

    const commonTooltipConfig = {
        callbacks: {
            title: function(tooltipItems) {
                const item = tooltipItems[0];
                let label = item.chart.data.labels[item.dataIndex];
                if (Array.isArray(label)) {
                    return label.join(' ');
                } else {
                    return label;
                }
            }
        }
    };

    const ctxWorkarounds = document.getElementById('workaroundsChart').getContext('2d');
    new Chart(ctxWorkarounds, {
        type: 'bar',
        data: {
            labels: [
                wrapLabel('Secondary Excel/Spreadsheets'),
                wrapLabel('External Webhooks for Logic'),
                wrapLabel('Physical Windshield Stickers'),
                wrapLabel('Custom Proprietary GUIs (CowPie)'),
                wrapLabel('Manual SQL Injection Scripts')
            ],
            datasets: [{
                label: 'Friction Level & Frequency of Use',
                data: [95, 75, 85, 60, 40],
                backgroundColor: '#06B6D4',
                borderRadius: 4
            }]
        },
        options: {
            responsive: true,
            maintainAspectRatio: false,
            plugins: {
                legend: { display: false },
                tooltip: commonTooltipConfig
            },
            scales: {
                y: { beginAtZero: true, max: 100, title: { display: true, text: 'Adoption / Friction Severity' } }
            }
        }
    });

    const ctxCompliance = document.getElementById('complianceChart').getContext('2d');
    new Chart(ctxCompliance, {
        type: 'doughnut',
        data: {
            labels: [
                wrapLabel('Documented PM Strategy in EAM'),
                wrapLabel('Actual Successful Field Execution')
            ],
            datasets: [{
                data: [80, 45],
                backgroundColor: ['#1E3A8A', '#F97316'],
                borderWidth: 2,
                borderColor: '#ffffff'
            }]
        },
        options: {
            responsive: true,
            maintainAspectRatio: false,
            cutout: '65%',
            plugins: {
                tooltip: commonTooltipConfig,
                legend: { position: 'bottom' }
            }
        }
    });

    const ctxRadar = document.getElementById('frictionRadarChart').getContext('2d');
    new Chart(ctxRadar, {
        type: 'radar',
        data: {
            labels: [
                wrapLabel('Labor Forecasting Accuracy'),
                wrapLabel('Inbox Clutter Management'),
                wrapLabel('Complex Interval Support (Fleet)'),
                wrapLabel('Administrative Efficiency (Nesting)'),
                wrapLabel('Technician Trust in System')
            ],
            datasets: [{
                label: 'Current Static EAM',
                data: [20, 10, 15, 25, 30],
                backgroundColor: 'rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2)',
                borderColor: '#EF4444',
                pointBackgroundColor: '#EF4444'
            },
            {
                label: 'Target Dynamic Scheduler',
                data: [90, 95, 100, 85, 90],
                backgroundColor: 'rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.2)',
                borderColor: '#10B981',
                pointBackgroundColor: '#10B981'
            }]
        },
        options: {
            responsive: true,
            maintainAspectRatio: false,
            scales: {
                r: { beginAtZero: true, max: 100 }
            },
            plugins: {
                tooltip: commonTooltipConfig
            }
        }
    });

    const ctxDegradation = document.getElementById('degradationChart').getContext('2d');
    new Chart(ctxDegradation, {
        type: 'line',
        data: {
            labels: ['Year 0', 'Year 2', 'Year 4', 'Year 6', 'Year 8', 'Year 10', 'Year 12', 'Year 14', 'Year 16'],
            datasets: [
                {
                    label: 'Rigid Assumption (Linear)',
                    data: [100, 87.5, 75, 62.5, 50, 37.5, 25, 12.5, 0],
                    borderColor: '#9CA3AF',
                    borderDash: [5, 5],
                    tension: 0,
                    fill: false
                },
                {
                    label: 'Actual Reality (Dynamic TSFM)',
                    data: [100, 98, 95, 90, 82, 60, 45, 15, 0],
                    borderColor: '#1E3A8A',
                    backgroundColor: 'rgba(30, 58, 138, 0.1)',
                    tension: 0.4,
                    fill: true
                },
                {
                    label: 'Minor Repair Event (Anomaly Detected)',
                    data: [null, null, null, null, null, 85, 70, 40, null],
                    borderColor: '#F97316',
                    borderWidth: 3,
                    pointBackgroundColor: '#F97316',
                    pointRadius: 5,
                    tension: 0.4,
                    fill: false
                }
            ]
        },
        options: {
            responsive: true,
            maintainAspectRatio: false,
            plugins: {
                tooltip: commonTooltipConfig,
                legend: { position: 'top' }
            },
            scales: {
                y: { beginAtZero: true, max: 100, title: { display: true, text: 'Asset Health Index (AHI)' } },
                x: { title: { display: true, text: 'Operational Lifespan' } }
            }
        }
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
